HEADWORD: Necrology
<hw>Ne*crol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Necrologies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Gr. <grk>nekro`s</grk>
a dead person + <ets>-logy</ets>: cf. F. <ets>n⟦eacute⟧crologie</ets>.
See <er>Necromancy</er>.]</ety> <def>An account of deaths, or of the
dead; a register of deaths; a collection of obituary notices.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

